open_spaces_details.description:
The Green Quarter is a landscape lead masterplan with a transformative vision to regenerate a former gasworks into a sustainable, nature-rich place which allows communities to thrive.

The landscape transitions from a formal square at the Central Hub to progressively softer and more biodiverse areas through Central Gardens as it progresses towards the Grand Union Canal and the Minet Country Park.
Water is drawn through the public realm a key unifying feature of the masterplan. The new masterplan establishes a green link from The Central Gardens to the Wetlands; an extensive biodiverse park and major play space. 
It provides an exemplar sustainable design by placing SuDS at the centre of the scheme, creating amenity and important habitat that allows people to connect with nature.

protected_spaces_details.description:
The towpath along the Grand Union Canal, which is identified as a Site of Importance for Nature Conservation (SINC), will be upgraded with improved connection delivered by the proposed development. 

A number of proposed Development Parcels are located in close proximity to the canal-side and are likely to overshadow the canal at certain parts of the day.
